= Fundraising

For better or for worse, the party cannot exist without money. There are a variety of ways we can gather money, from embezzling from state governments, to securing industrial support, to membership dues.

Dues are based on the amount of dissent in the party. The amount of resources the party gets at the end of the year is reduced by dissent.

- @maintain: Maintain our current dues.
- @reduce: Reduce dues.
- @increase: Increase dues.
- @increase_high: Increase dues further
- @industrial: Secure a loan from the industrialists
- @state_government: Embezzle money from the Prussian State Government
- @easy_discard

---

@maintain
subtitle: We will gain [+ dues +] resources a year.

We will maintain our current dues.

---

@reduce
subtitle: We will gain [+ dues - 1 +] resources a year.
choose-if: dues > 1
on-arrival:
  dues -= 1
  left_dissent -= 8
  center_dissent -= 8
  christian_dissent -= 8
  clerical_dissent -= 8
  right_dissent -= 8

Our current members appreciate this gesture, but no one decides to join a party because of the low dues.

---

@increase
subtitle: We will gain [+ dues + 1 +] resources a year.
view-if: dues < 5
on-arrival:
  dues += 1
  catholics_z -= 5
  workers_z -= 4
  new_middle_z -= 4
  old_middle_z -= 4
  left_dissent += 5
  center_dissent += 5
  christian_dissent += 5
  clerical_dissent += 5
  right_dissent += 5

Our members grumble at this, and some of the less committed members leave. But now, we will have access to additional resources.

---

@increase_high
subtitle: We will gain [+ dues + 1 +] resources a year. Dues are already high; this may cost members.
view-if: dues >= 5
on-arrival:
  dues += 1
  catholics_z -= 9
  workers_z -= 8
  new_middle_z -= 6
  old_middle_z -= 6
  left_dissent += 8
  center_dissent += 8
  christian_dissent += 8
  clerical_dissent += 8
  right_dissent += 8

Increasing our already high dues has outraged the membership. Many leave, and all factions voice significant dissent. At least the finances are strong?

---

@industrial
subtitle: The industrialists have traditionally prioritized the liberal parties. Maybe that can change? +2 resources
choose-if: dvp_relation >= 50
unavailable-subtitle: The industrialists do not trust us enough as our relations with the DVP are insufficient.
on-arrival:
  resources += 2
  old_middle_z += 3
  workers_z -= 8
  left_dissent += 8

